External environment of a business and its formation. Key factors influencing entrepreneurship and their relevance on an example of a specific organization.  Principles of entrepreneurship policy in Estonia and the EU. Business support system in Estonia. The essence of innovation and its role in the society and business activity.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide the knowledge about business environment (incl. external environment of business and its formation), and the key factors that influence the operation of a business, the relationship between economic policy and development of businesses, entrepreneurial behaviour, innovation and its role in business activity and society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) analyses micro- and macroeconomic factors of the business environment in the context of a specific organization; 2) knows the principles of entrepreneurship policy in Estonia and the EU; 3) understands the Estonian national business support system and is able to adapt it to specific needs of an organization; 4) understands the role of innovative entrepreneurship in the society and the role of innovation in  business processes; 5) understands the role of creativity in entrepreneurship, including innovation and can analyse the business issues creatively and systemically.
